summary: This mod adds thousands of new trees to Skyrim.  Original version is fantasy based, Fall Forest version is more realistic.  Billboards available for TES5LODGen and DynDOLOD. Updated 6/5/17 see changelog for details
descriptionHtml:
[center]
[size=6]
[/size][size=6][b]Fantasy Forest Overhaul[/b][/size]


[youtube]-ayQk0HSTtY[/youtube][/center][center]big thanks to Hodi for making this video[/center][center][b][size=5]

[/size][/b][/center] 
[size=4][b][u]NOTE TO SSE USERS:[/u][/b]  This mod is no longer available for the special edition.  You will need to convert this mod to SSE yourself.  The textures and models used just do not look good in the special edition and I do not have to photoshop and nifskope skills (yet) to update them and improve their look.  I am no longer playing the special edition and prefer the 32 bit Skyrim for many reasons, therefore I will not be spending time to mod a game I have no interest in playing.[/size][size=5]  



[/size]

[size=5]General Info:
[/size]
[size=3]- version 3.2 and higher no longer adds trees to Solstheim. 

- USLEEP now required

- billboards for the mod are now available as a separate file.  I highly suggest using TES5LODGen or DynDOLOD to make the mods you use compatible with this one (Simply Bigger Trees, Realistic Aspen Trees, Dark Fantasy Overhaul, Enhanced Landscapes, etc)
[/size]
[size=3]- This mod increases the density of trees in Skyrim and also creates whole new forested areas.   Aspen trees come in 7 different colors and Pine Trees come in 6 different colors.  Version 3 adds colorful snowy pines, dead pines, and ash covered pines.

- [b]The original edition[/b] of this mod replaces the vanilla aspen trees with green and purple colored ones. Version 3 does no longer replaces vanilla pines with 3AM dead ones, however [/size][size=3][size=3]it still contains some dead pines I've added.
[/size]
- [b]The Fall Forest edition[/b] replaces all vanilla aspens with brown, burnt and a few green varieties.   This version does not replace any vanilla pine trees but still contains some dead pines I've added. 
[/size]
[img width=432,height=298]https://68.media.tumblr.com/0bd1f735eff2137c46b171cc4be79b50/tumblr_of5jowQjMP1s2ptqso4_540.jpg[/img][img width=437,height=289]https://66.media.tumblr.com/69d323418b409b1cfe7105cff62b1dde/tumblr_of5jowQjMP1s2ptqso5_540.jpg[/img][img width=430,height=298]https://68.media.tumblr.com/4af7f6e3b6120346d472c2d7f9d44f62/tumblr_of5jowQjMP1s2ptqso8_540.jpg[/img][img width=440,height=298]https://66.media.tumblr.com/e9c8f64e61b96214a2e50c4cac4b443f/tumblr_of5jowQjMP1s2ptqso6_540.jpg[/img]
[img width=438,height=298]https://66.media.tumblr.com/26d5030d16b96743d41d280809485757/tumblr_oeuwo105DQ1s2ptqso1_540.jpg[/img][img width=442,height=298]https://66.media.tumblr.com/684945d651fc7820ea0c60a5441b8738/tumblr_oeuvqeBsyt1s2ptqso2_540.jpg[/img]








[size=5]Overhaul Details - Fantasy based Original Version
[/size]
[size=3]The Rift:  Trees in the Rift are now green and purple with more added purple aspens along the Morrowind border.  Ground cover and falling leaves have been changed to match the tree leaves.

Falkreath: 20% of the vanilla trees have been replaced by dead ones (goes for every hold).  Golden and Yellow Pine groves border the Reach.  Two new types of pines have been added to the forest but they do not replace vanilla pines. Green aspens now border Lake Ilinalta

The Reach:  Added a dead forest with more reach trees and also added some dead aspens.  The dead forest runs from Markarth to Falkreath.  The northern Reach is now an early fall forest (green and colored aspens) and runs from Markarth to Dragonbridge. 

Haafingar:  The southern tier of the hold is now a late fall forest with little to no green aspens, and also a few dead aspens.  The pine forest now has golden, evergreen and red pine trees...version 3 now has snowy red and yellow pines

Hjaalmarch: The Marshes now have two types of mushrooms (more in future updates) and the shorelines are lined with multi-colored reeds as well as a few flowers from Morrowind.   Golden pines and purple aspens also dot the landscape. 

The Pale:  A dead pine forest is now on the outskirts of Dawnstar, with more snowy pines scattered around the hold

Eastmarch:  Expanded the size of Witchmist Grove (3-4 times more trees) and added an aspen forest along the border to The Rift.  Colorful dead pine trees and some needle-less dead pines have been added to the hot springs area

Winterhold: Added some snowy pines along the path to Winterhold and also some near Saarthal.

Whiterun: No changes except replace some vanilla pines

If you prefer fall colored Aspens in the Reach instead of the green and purple ones, install my [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/79630/?]Peak Aspen replacer mod[/url] after you install this edition (GFOWH compatibility coming soon)
[/size]










[size=5]Overhaul Details -More realistic Fall Forest Version
[/size]
[size=5][size=3]The Rift:  Trees in the Rift are now fall colors (brown, dark red, orange and a few green varieties) with a few added purple and brown aspens along the Morrowind border. 

Falkreath:   Golden and Yellow Pine groves border the Reach.  Fall Colored aspens now border Lake Ilinalta.  [/size][/size]
[size=5][size=3][size=3] Two new types of pines have been added to the forest but they do not replace vanilla pines.[/size]

The Reach:  All reach trees and dead aspens have been replaced by fall colored aspens, as well as hundreds of added aspens.  [u]The entire Reach is now a fall forest[/u]

Haafingar:  The southern tier of the hold is now a late fall forest with little to no green aspens.  The pine forest now has golden, evergreen and red pine trees.  Version 3 includes snowy colored pines.

Hjaalmarch: The Marshes now have two types of mushrooms (more in future updates)
and the shorelines are lined with multi-colored reeds as well as a few flowers from Morrowind.   Golden pines and purple aspens also dot the
landscape. 

The Pale:  A dead pine forest is now on the outskirts of Dawnstar (this will be larger in future updates).  New colorful snowy pines have been added all across the hold.

Eastmarch:  [/size][/size][size=5][size=3][size=3]Expanded the size of Witchmist Grove (3-4 times more trees) and added an aspen forest along the border to The Rift.  Colorful
dead pine trees and some needle-less dead pines have been added to the
hot springs area[/size]

Winterhold: [/size][/size][size=5][size=3][size=3]Added some snowy pines along the path to Winterhold and also some near Saarthal.[/size]

Whiterun: No changes [/size]




[/size]

[size=3][size=5]Requirements:[/size] legendary edition and [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/71214/?]Unofficial Legendary Patch (USLEEP)[/url]
[/size]






[size=5]Compatibility: [/size]

[size=3]- This mod is compatible with [b]Skyrim Flora Overhaul (SFO), Dark Fantasy Overhaul (DFO), Realistic Aspen Tree (RAT) and other mods IF you use TES5LODGen or DynDOLOD[/b].  Billboards are available.   


- [b]Whiterun has[/b] not been touched with new trees.  Therefore, any mod that adds objects and trees to those ares is compatible with this mod.  This mod is out of box compatible with [b]The Great Forest of Whiterun Hold[/b] IF you use TES5LODGen or DynDOLOD.

- [b]Interiors [/b]have not been touched so all [b]city and town overhauls[/b] will be compatible.  This mod does not add grass or shrubs so [b]ALL grass mods[/b] are compatible. 

- Disable any weird looking or floating trees with the [url=https://forums.nexusmods.com/index.php?/topic/1111601-using-the-console-to-remove-trees-in-game/]command console [/url].  Mods that make major changes to landscapes or add objects to overhauled areas may cause issues, so please let me know if you have a tree growing inside your custom house or town mod.











[size=5]KNOWN COMPATIBLE MODS:[/size]
Falkreath Overlook Farmhouse (I highly recommend this mod!)
Halamshiral
Mountain Ridge Rest
TES Arena Legendary Cities
JK Skyrim
Open Cities
Shezrie's Old Hroldan
Dark Fantasy Overhaul (including swamps)
Aspen Lodge
Castle Strunmah
Castle Riverwood
Daedric Castle
Folkstead
Nyhus
Moon and Star
The Asteria
all Solstheim mods
Frost Ivy Glade (player home on Solstheim)
Snowdrift Manor
Dolmen Ruins (delete any trees growing out of stone with command console)
all Whiterun mods
Enhanced Landcapes v1.4 - Highly recommended



Note for Enhanced Landscapes users: I have tested FFO with Enhanced Landscapes and it is a great combination with minimal overlapping and clipping using current versions.  Use the command console to disable any overlapping objects and clipping trees[/size][size=3]

[/size]









[size=4][size=5]Installation:[/size]

- Both the original and Fall Forest versions have the same options below
[/size]
[size=3]1) Vanilla (no DynDOLOD or TES5Edit):  Choose the vanilla tree LOD version of this mod.  Install manually or with mod manager.  Tree LOD has been generated.  Pick either the original version or the fall forest version

2) Vanilla + [/size][size=3][size=3]Skyrim Flora Overhaul[/size] (with no DynDOLOD or TES5Edit): choose the  [size=3]Skyrim Flora Overhaul[/size] version of this mod in the main files section under the same name.  Pick either the original version OR the fall forest version

3) with other tree overhauls or landscape overhauls that change or add trees to Skyrim (TES5Edit or DynDOLOD required!!!):  in the optional files section choose the 'LODGen version'.  billboards are included with this version.  Install Fantasy Forest Overhaul AFTER all other overhauls and their respective billboards, then run TES5LODGen or DynDOLOD. [/size]











[size=4]
[size=5]My TO-DO list for future updates
[/size][/size]1) Add new textures and meshes for colored Pines (Vurt and GKB)
2)  Add more non-vanilla trees, living and dead
3) Add new textures and meshes for Aspens (Lush and Tamu75)
[s]
[/s]









[size=5]Change Log:[/size]

Fall Forest:
1.1: fixed bug where colored aspen and dead pine billboards were not visible

1.2: fixed a mismatched billboard on treeaspen03 for the fall forest edition

2.0: increased the size of the haunted forest outside of Dawnstar and added more living and half dead pines.  Finished overhauling Haafingar with fall aspens and also red and wintergreen pines.  Added new mushrooms and more reeds to the swamps of Hjaalmarch.  Increased the tree count in Eastmarch, around Lake Ilinalta, and the northern Reach.

2.1: Fixed overlapping and obstructive plants, mushrooms and trees for compatibility with JK Skyrim, TES Legendary Cities, Shezrie's Old Hroldan, Mountain Ridge Rest, Halamshiral, and the swamps of Morthal for Dark Fantasy Overhaul

2.2:  added LODGen versions with high resolution (indistinguishable) custom billboards

2.3: reduced the saturation and brightness (yet again) for distant aspen trees (and also their corresponding billboards for the LODGen versions) to better match their close up 3-D models

2.4: 
- Replaced dead winter aspens with fall aspens for the fall forest edition (distant trees now match their close up models 100%)
- increased the quality of ALL the distant trees to better match their close up models
- fixed floating aspens and reach trees in Haafingar and the Reach
- added another fall forest near the orc stronghold on the border of Haafingar and The Reach
- USLEEP no longer required LODGen version

2.5:
- removed USLEEP dependence for all versions
- recolored billboards and reduced saturation and brightness for better looking distant trees
- cleaned .esp with TES5Edit

3.0
- added 50 new types of colored pine trees (15 new snowy lite, 15 snowy, and 20 new dead pines)
- overhauled Solstheim with dead, ash covered and snowy pines (I added 20 new colored ashy pines)
- FIXED ALL MISSING WATER and a few other boo-boos due to my bad editing.
- eastmarch hotsprings overhauled with 20 new types of dead pines and also 3AM pines
- added some forests to winterhold
- added dark and evergreen pine trees to the pine forests in Falkreath, Haafingar, and the northern reach
- fixed a bunch of floaters
- removed dead pine trees as replacements for vanilla pines. 

3.1
 - out of box support for Great Forest of Whiterun Hold discontinued.  If you use that mod you must now generate your own LOD
 - out of box support added for Skyrim Flora Overhaul
 - all floating moss has been removed from the reach trees in the Fall Forest edition
 - black dirt and purple leaves have been removed from the Rift

3.1A
 - removed all ITMs and dirty edits
 - esp files for 3.1A now has better compatibility for Enhanced Landscapes


3.5
 - fixed a missing bridge and removed some aspens that clip with rocks and mountains
 - updated tree LOD for SFO and removed "pop-in" from SFO pines

[size=5]Credits: This mod was made using the Bethesda Creation Kit and the following modders resources:[/size]

1) Mentha's [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/26192/?]More Colorful Trees[/url] for all the new aspens and pines
2) [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/59632/?]Phitt's Sheogorad Resources[/url] for the marshmerrow and stoneflower plants
3)[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/61932/?] 3AM trees[/url] for the dead pines and vurt for the textures
4) Zilav's [url=http://]TreeLOD billboard generator[/url] allowed me to create some of the billboards
5) [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/62698/?]TES5LODGen[/url] by Zilav for creating the LOD files (you should be using this too, or [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/59721/?]DynDOLOD[/url]!!)
6) Bethesda for some vanilla meshes and textures that i just recolored with photoshop

[/size]
